  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is a storage-level pruning ceiling: the existing ddate zonemap block granularity is too coarse, so many mixed-date blocks still force row-wise ddate checks in main_scan. Strategy category E (storage extension): build and register a reusable fine-grained num.ddate zonemap at 4096-row blocks, use it as the first pruning structure with the same deferred-load anti-join pipeline from iter 3, and keep pre index and join-key column loading conditional on survivor presence so scan work is reduced without reintroducing heavy posting-index setup overhead.",
